## Use Case 3: Academy Awards Analysis and Predictive Insights

### Description
Film industry analysts, award strategists, and entertainment journalists require detailed information about Academy Awards nominations and wins across history. This enables temporal analysis, trend identification, and insights into award-winning patterns.

### Business Goals
- Analyze historical patterns in Academy Awards nominations and wins
- Identify which film characteristics correlate with award recognition
- Track professionals' award success rates and categories
- Support award season predictions and strategy discussions

### Key Requirements Enabled
- R37: Catalog all Academy Award ceremonies with ceremony numbers and years
- R38: Identify all movies nominated across all ceremonies
- R39: Retrieve complete list of professionals (actors, directors, producers) nominated for awards
- R40: Enumerate all award categories to enable category-specific analysis
- R41: Access ceremony years for temporal trend analysis
- R42: Determine winners vs. nominees for success rate calculations
- R1-R4, R11-R12: Link award data back to movies and their metadata

### Example Queries
- "Which movies released in year Y were nominated for Best Picture?"
- "How many times has Director X been nominated? How many times won?"
- "What are the most common genres among Best Picture winners?"
- "Which professionals received nominations in the 88th Academy Awards ceremony and who won?"
